âœ… Steps to Replicate Specific Databases
ğŸ“ 1. Edit MySQL Configuration on the Replica (my.ini or my.cnf)
Add the following under the [mysqld] section on the replica:

replicate-do-db=database1
replicate-do-db=database2

ğŸ“ You can repeat replicate-do-db for each database you want to replicate.


ğŸ“Œ Important Notes:
These filters only affect the replica â€” the master sends everything, but the replica applies only what matches.

Make sure your application uses the correct database explicitly (via USE dbname; or dbname.tablename) in every statement â€” otherwise filtering may not work as expected.


âš ï¸ Example of Bad Case
USE database1;
INSERT INTO table1 VALUES (...);

This may not replicate if filtering is strict.
Better to do:
INSERT INTO database1.table1 VALUES (...);

ğŸ§ª 2. Restart MySQL on the Replica
After editing the config file:

systemctl restart mysql   # Linux
net stop mysql && net start mysql   # Windows

ğŸ” 3. Check if Itâ€™s Working
Use on the replica:

SHOW SLAVE STATUS\G

Look for:

Seconds_Behind_Master

No errors in Last_Error

ğŸ”„ Alternative: Use CHANGE REPLICATION FILTER (MySQL 8.0.23+)

CHANGE REPLICATION FILTER REPLICATE_DO_DB = (database1, database2);

This dynamically sets replication filters without editing the config file (MySQL 8.0.23 or later).

âœ… How to Replicate Only Specific Tables
You use the replicate-do-table option in the replica (slave) configuration.

ğŸ”§ Step-by-Step
1. Edit MySQL Config File on the Replica
On Windows, this is typically my.ini.
On Linux, itâ€™s usually /etc/my.cnf or /etc/mysql/my.cnf.

Add under [mysqld]:
replicate-do-table=your_database.table1
replicate-do-table=your_database.table2

2. Restart MySQL Service on Replica
After modifying the config:

Optional (MySQL 8.0.23+): Use SQL to Change Filters
Instead of editing the config file:

CHANGE REPLICATION FILTER REPLICATE_DO_TABLE = ('db1.table1', 'db2.table2');

ğŸ” Types of Replication in MySQL

| Replication Type                               | Description                                                                                                                              | Use Case                                             |
| ---------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| ğŸ”¹ **Asynchronous Replication**                | Default; master sends binlog to replica; replica applies when it can.                                                                    | âœ… Simple, used when minor lag is acceptable.         |
| ğŸ”¸ **Semi-Synchronous Replication**            | Master waits for **at least one replica** to acknowledge receipt before committing.                                                      | âœ… Safer than async, ensures some data durability.    |
| ğŸŸ¢ **Group Replication** (InnoDB Cluster)      | Multi-master, built-in conflict handling, automatic failover.                                                                            | âœ… HA, fault-tolerant, cloud-friendly.                |
| ğŸ§  **Multi-Source Replication**                | One replica receives data from multiple masters.                                                                                         | Used in data warehousing or sharded apps.            |
| ğŸ“‚ **Row-based, Statement-based, Mixed-mode**  | Formats of binlog: <br>â€¢ **Row-based (RBR)** â€“ logs actual data <br>â€¢ **Statement-based (SBR)** â€“ logs SQL <br>â€¢ **Mixed** â€“ combination | **Row-based** is most preferred for safety/accuracy. |
| ğŸ”€ **Replica Filtering (Partial Replication)** | Replicate only selected databases/tables.                                                                                                | âœ… Custom sync, reduce load.                          |
| ğŸ§° **MySQL Clone Plugin** (8.0+)               | For provisioning a new replica from another instance.                                                                                    | âœ… Fast initial sync without dump/import.             |

